## 3. Structs

The Rust Book says structs are for grouping related values and naming each piece of data so the meaning is clear. ([Rust Documentation][3])

```rust
struct Book {
    title: String,
    author: String,
    pages: u32,
}

fn main() {
    let book = Book {
        title: String::from("Apple"),
        author: String::from("Steve Jobs"),
        pages: 549,
    };

    println!("{}", book.title);
    println!("{}", book.pages);
}
```

Structs are the Rust equivalent of a named record or object.

### Real-world example: student

```rust
struct Student {
    name: String,
    languages: Vec<String>,
    active: bool,
}

fn main() {
    let student = Student {
        name: String::from("Mike"),
        languages: vec![
            String::from("English"),
            String::from("French"),
            String::from("German"),
        ],
        active: true,
    };

    println!("{}", student.name);
    println!("{:?}", student.languages);
}
```

