## 4. Hash sets and hash maps

Rust’s `std::collections` docs group `HashMap` under maps and `HashSet` under sets. `HashSet` stores unique values, and `HashMap` stores key-value pairs. ([Rust Documentation][1])

### HashSet

```rust
use std::collections::HashSet;

fn main() {
    let skills = HashSet::from([
        "boxing",
        "Muay Thai",
        "karate",
        "Muay Thai",
    ]);

    println!("{:?}", skills);
    println!("{}", skills.contains("boxing"));
}
```

Even though `"Muay Thai"` appears twice, the set only keeps one copy.

### HashMap

```rust
use std::collections::HashMap;

fn main() {
    let mut book = HashMap::new();
    book.insert("title", "Apple");
    book.insert("author", "Steve Jobs");

    println!("{:?}", book);
    println!("{}", book["title"]);
}
```

For Week 2, the most important thing is:

* `HashSet` for uniqueness
* `HashMap` for key-value lookup

