## Indexing reminder

Rust vectors use **zero-based indexing**.

```rust
fn main() {
    let colors = vec!["red", "blue", "green"];
    println!("{}", colors[0]);
    println!("{}", colors[1]);
    println!("{}", colors[2]);
}
```

But tuples use `.0`, `.1`, `.2`.

