### B. Destructure a tuple

Rust patterns can destructure tuples, and the Rust Book’s patterns section covers this broader pattern syntax. ([Rust Documentation][4])

```rust
fn main() {
    let user_profile = ("Anthony", 32, true);
    let (name, age, active) = user_profile;

    println!("{}", name);
    println!("{}", age);
    println!("{}", active);
}
```

### C. HashSet membership

```rust
use std::collections::HashSet;

fn main() {
    let skills = HashSet::from(["python", "sql", "python"]);
    println!("{}", skills.contains("python"));
}
```

